.TH LIGHTNING-INSTALL 1 "2026" "bitcoin stack" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-install \- install the Core Lightning daemon (top-level alias)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning install
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Install the underlying
.B lightningd
(Core Lightning) binary. Harmonized across the stack (FEAT-307),
.B install
is a top-level verb on every command \(em
.BR bitcoin (1),
.BR lightning (1),
.BR fulcrum (1),
and
.BR monero (1)
all expose
.BI "<cmd> install" .
.PP
This is a thin alias that delegates to
.B lightning daemon install
(which keeps working too); see
.BR lightning-daemon (1)
for the full set of install sources and flags.
.SH OPTIONS
See
.BR lightning-daemon (1)
\(em the options are identical
.RB ( --from ,
.BR --tag ,
.BR --system ,
.BR --yes ,
.BR --force ,
.BR --dry-run ).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR lightning-daemon (1),
.BR lightning (1)
.SH HISTORY
Top-level install added in the FEAT-307 harmonization.
.SH STANDARDS
Core Lightning packaging conventions.
.SH FILES
None of its own; see
.BR lightning-daemon (1).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
See
.BR lightning-daemon (1).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0
on success; non-zero on a failed install.
